9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1119, L.D. 1684, “An Act to Exclude
10 from Eligibility for a Community Confinement Monitoring Program a Person Serving a
11 Sentence for Certain Domestic Violence Crimes”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Implement Additional Criteria and Processes for the Supervised
14 Community Confinement Program'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 34-A MRSA §3036-A, sub-§2-A, ¶B, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 376, §3,
18 is amended to read:
19 B. The process must reflect best practices for evaluating the likelihood of a prisoner's
20 completion of supervised community confinement if transferred and must provide
21 guidance to department staff as to how to apply the established criteria when
22 conducting the evaluation. The process must require, when information is obtained by
23 the department from persons in the community for the purpose of determining whether
24 to approve a prisoner for transfer to supervised community confinement, that those
25 persons be informed of the prisoner's fulfillment of expectations as to conduct,
26 fulfillment of expectations as to work, education, and rehabilitation programs assigned
27 in the case plan and other rehabilitative efforts and accomplishments. The process
28 must include consideration of any information provided by the Office of Victim
29 Services, as established in section 1214, and, if requested by the office, allow for an
30 extension of time necessary for the office to make additional good faith efforts to
31 contact any victims of the crimes for which the prisoner is incarcerated. The process
32 must include an evaluation of whether the proposed supervised community
33 confinement plan is responsive to reasonable safety concerns raised by persons in the
34 community, including any victims of the crimes for which the prisoner is incarcerated.
35 The process must also include the right of a prisoner who is eligible for transfer to
