7 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
8 number to read consecutively.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
1111 changes the title. The amendment requires that the process and criteria for determining a
1122 Department of Corrections prisoner's eligibility in the supervised community confinement
1133 program includes considering input from the Office of Victim Services within the
1144 department and further requires that a prisoner's supervised community confinement
1155 program plan is responsive to reasonable community and victim concerns. The amendment
1166 also provides that the process and criteria must include review and consideration of any
1177 validated, evidence-based domestic violence risk assessment for a prisoner who is
1188 incarcerated for a crime committed against a family or household member or dating partner.
1199 The amendment requires a prisoner who is released to the supervised community
2200 confinement program to continue paying any victim restitution similar to what the prisoner
2211 would have paid if the prisoner had stayed in a department correctional facility.
